	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85572><span id= >killmorestuff</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>yes cleric's do get a pet if you can call it <br>a pet <br>here is the info <br>Name:&nbsp;&nbsp;Unswerving Hammer of Faith <br>Level:  54 <br>Mana:  600 <br>Class:  Conjuration <br>Era:  Ruins Of Kunark <br>Vendor(s):  Brinaa Darkpact <br>Frist Furtun <br> <br>Approx Spell Cost:   Unknown <br>Researchable:        No <br>Type:                Summon a No-Rent Miscellaneous Object <br>Max Duration:  Instant <br>Casting Time:  6 seconds <br>Recast Time:  Instant <br>Actual Effects: Summon: Hammer <br><br>Description: This spell summons an animated hammer for the Cleric. The pet has only 100 HP so it is recomended not to use in solo type combat. The animation seems usefull only for extra damage such as fighting a god/dragon.<br>This spell must have an NPC target to cast. The hammer will fly straight to the target and fight until it takes 100 points of damage or the monster dies. The Hammer will die once the target is dead, if it lives that long. <br><br>The Animated Hammer can be buffed and healed. <br> <br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
